SIMPLE: tracker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tracker
<hw>Track"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, tracks or pursues, as a man or dog that follows
game.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And of the <qex>trackers</qex> of the deer⟦br⟧
Scarce half the lessening pack was near.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>In the organ, a light strip of
wood connecting (in path) a key and a pallet, to communicate motion by
pulling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tracklayer</ent>⟦br⟧
